text.tspan: Income from financial activities in 2020 totalled
RUB 969 million and comprised interest from
depositing temporarily idle cash and other finance
income. The 22% decrease in interest income relative
to 2019 was primarily due to the lower interest rates
in the market for the placement of idle cash.
Freight One’s finance costs over the 12 months
of 2020 totalled RUB 2,222 million and comprised
expenditure on bank loans and financial leasing
liabilities. The 35% decrease in expenditure relative
to 2019 is the result of a reduction in the amount
of principal debt owed on bonds and bank loans.
This led to a reduction in net finance costs
